1 provisions on or after that date. Notwithstanding G.S. 105-282.1(a)(2)a., an owner of low- or
2 moderate-income rental housing property that is exempt under G.S. 105-278.6(a)(8) as of the
3 effective date of this act must, by December 31, 2026, reapply for the exemption, providing the
4 assessor of the taxing unit with any necessary documentation for compliance consistent with this
5 act. Reapplication under this section is considered an application under G.S. 105-278.7A(f), as
6 enacted by this act. Failure to meet this requirement within the time limit subjects the property
7 to discovery under G.S. 105-312.
